nodes.bodyText:
cells is a varargs argument, this will cause you to have a Row with multiple cells.
 List.of("foo", "bar").toArray()
$2 ==> Object[2] { "foo", "bar" }


var row = new RowN(List.of("foo", "bar").toArray())
row.numColumns(); -> this will be 2, instead of 1

What you want is something like this:
var row = new RowN(new Object[] { List.of("foo", "bar").toArray() });
row.numColumns(); -> this will be 1

